  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain and update accounting records and files.</li>\n  <li>Process payments, invoices, income and receipts, and enter data into accounting software.</li>\n  <li>Assist in month-end and year-end closing activities.</li>\n  <li>Handle reimbursement claims.</li>\n  <li>Monitor accounts payable and receivable to ensure timely payments and collections.</li>\n  <li>Assist with preparation for audits and resolve any discrepancies.</li>\n  <li>Submit CHAS claims accurately and in a timely manner via MOH’s eClaim system.</li>\n  <li>Monitor the status of CHAS claims and follow up on pending or rejected claims.</li>\n  <li>Reconcile CHAS payments received with internal patient billing records.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with vendors, clients, and internal departments on financial matters.</li>\n  <li>Support the Finance Manager with ad-hoc tasks and projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum diploma in Business, Accounting, Finance, or related field.</li>\n  <li>Excellent organizational skills with meticulous attention to detail.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and prioritize tasks effectively.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in a similar role will be an advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
